The government was today expressing alarm over the rising number of teenage pregnancies after an unprecedented number of female candidates sat their KCPE examination in the maternity ward Education Cabinet Secretary Amina Mohammed and Principal Secretary Dr. Belio Kipsang’ drew the attention of the nation on the  on worrying trend with a stern warning against anyone found to have impregnated the under age girls. The ministry is now expected to investigate the extent of the situation and give a report for further action.  